FidoNews 12-31                 Page:  2                    31 Jul 1995


    I spent a lovely day listening to blues on our downtown park
today.  A band from Chigago, one from Detpoit, and a local band.
Wonder full music.

    We live in the center of the city, a place of about a
quarter million people, about 100 kilometers out of Toronto.
Met a bunch of neighbours that I had not met before, and they
all ended up back at our place, playing music, drinking beer,
and talking about the net.

    Funny, I kept thinking about how my neighbours are other
people that I know, and converse with.  Borders are such silly
damned things.
