Subject: Fidonews viewer
From: Shawn McMahon (1:3806/10)

- Original by Shawn McMahon in area R19SYSOP.
- Forwarded by Shawn McMahon using Sqed/32.
- Mein Luftkissenfahrzeug ist voller Aale.
- Please direct all replies to Shawn McMahon at 1:3806/10.

I've just obtained a public domain program that should end the
Fidonews content controversy once and for all, assuming that
those who don't like it are actually offended by the content and
not just trying to exercise control.

It's a Fidonews viewer with a twit filter (won't show you
articles from people you don't like at all) and a word/phrase
filter. (Nuke them pesky words you don't like.)

The archive includes source code, and a 16-bit "family-mode"
executable that will run under both DOS and OS/2.  It has
configurable colors and etc.

Archive  name is FNEWS.ZIP, and I'll be uploading it to
1:3806/11. He normally lets me make things available for FREQ
through his system, so it should be available by the time you
read this.

It comes pre-set to nuke articles from Bob Germer and Steve
Winter, and to bleep out the obscene words "religion" and
"politics." <g>

These settings are completely configurable.
